<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-11-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="899" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d899">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Senor
                                    <persName type="to">Ojeda</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-11-12"><hi rend="italic">November 12,
                                    1902</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 4.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 5th instant, protesting against certain
                            proceedings taken by the <pb facs="1043" n="963" xml:id="pg_963"/>
                            police and in the municipal court of Pensacola against the captain and
                            members of the crew of the Spanish steamship <hi rend="italic">Leonora.</hi></p>
                        <p>I have the honor to say in reply that I have asked the governor of
                            Florida for a report on the matter, on the receipt of which the question
                            will be considered.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>